$head Step 6: Checking Install$$
$index check, install$$
$index install, check$$
Make sure OMhelp is functioning correctly by loading the file
$syntax/
	/parent/\omhelp\omh\htm\getstarted.htm
/$$
into your web browser. 
This should be a local copy of the web page
$pre
	$$
$href%http://www.seanet.com/~bradbell/omhelp/getstarted.htm%$$.


$head Step 7: Display Latex Mathematics$$
If you are going to use the $xref/latex/$$ command for displaying
mathematics, you will need a browser that supports MathML.
You can download and install the
$href%http://www.mozilla.org%Mozilla%$$ browser for this purpose.
Another option is to use 
MS Internet Explorer with the
Mathplayer plug in
which is freely available from
$href%http://www.dessci.com/webmath/mathplayer%Design Science%$$.
	
